>>> np.random.seed(123)
>>> a = np.random.rand(2, 2)
>>> b = np.random.rand(2, 5)
>>> c = np.random.rand(5, 2)
>>> path_info = np.einsum_path('ij,jk,kl->il', a, b, c, optimize='greedy')
>>> print(path_info[0])
['einsum_path', (1, 2), (0, 1)]
>>> print(path_info[1])
 Complete contraction:  ij,jk,kl->il # may vary
 Naive scaling:  4

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
scaling                  current                                remaining
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3                   kl,jk->jl                                ij,jl->il
